status_message:
How can we truly know the age of the Earth?

Update: It has come to our attention that there are several factual errors in this video. We would like to apologize and correct them: This video covers the oldest-known materials from Earth itself: 4.4 billion-year-old zircons.  While these amazing crystals don't tell us how old the Earth is, they are a key piece of evidence in Earth's geologic history and help support the meteorite-based age of our planet.
